    {
      "id": "f960cb2f75010e392fd51acc888ec788dfa2b64e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-03-05 20:57:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI'd like the commit message to also explain what the patch changes to fix the problem, not just describe the symptom.  (I'm glad it does describe the symptom, though.)\n\nSomething like: \"When there is no fid-in-dirent on the '..' dentry, the previous patch would not get the ea for the '..' dentry unless the parent was a remote directory.\"\n\nI am also a bit concerned about why we don't see this problem in el6 testing.\nAdding fid-in-dirent to the \"..\" dentry of an existing directory without fid-in-dirent is not possible except when the directory is moved (and even that is special cased, see LU-5626 for details)...\nBut my understanding is that for a new file system formatted with dirdata on from the beginning, all the \"..\" dentries should have 'fid-in-dirent' from when they are created.\n\nDo we understand why this isn't the case for ldiskfs on el7 but not el6?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2c0af3c05ffd2a6c547eaad516ce86cc64a4e946",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-03-05 20:59:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nNote that I agree that the fix looks correct.  I'll +1 this specific patch with the commit message fix and move my concerns about the missing fid-in-dirent information to LU-5022 if not answered here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
